1
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:37,600
When you took that grenade for me,

2
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:38,479
I looked up

3
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,800
and saw behind you,

4
00:01:39,960 --> 00:01:41,160
stood a little nurse.

5
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:42,840
She was quite pretty,

6
00:01:43,039 --> 00:01:44,280
a real beauty.

7
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:47,000
And the way she looked at people was different.

8
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:47,560
She's coming.

9
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:48,400
She's coming.

10
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:50,479
You wily old soldier,

11
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,800
don't get any funny ideas.

12
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:53,880
Her name is Han Xiaoyue.

13
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:55,840
Her man died on the Shanghai Battlefield.

14
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:56,800
She is nice to all the wounded.

15
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,259
Treats everyone the same.

16
00:01:59,039 --> 00:01:59,720
You guys,

17
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,480
who let you sneak out?

18
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:03,040
Get back inside now.

19
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:03,680
Time for your shots

20
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,560
and your medicine.

21
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:05,090
Hurry up.

22
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:06,080
Miss Xiaoyue,

23
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,680
are you going to give us the shots yourself?

24
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,240
Yes,

25
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:10,560
one by one.

26
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:11,800
Let's go.

27
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:12,600
Hurry up.

28
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:13,280
Hurry.

29
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:14,760
Hold him.

30
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:16,360
Hold him.

31
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,620
Come on, give me a hand.

32
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:19,000
Miss Xiaoyue,

33
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:21,120
I have a through-and-through wound,

34
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,579
and my butt is injured too.

35
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:25,200
Do you think it's appropriate to inject there?

36
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:26,760
It is.

37
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:29,320
I'll give you a through-and-through shot.

38
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:31,980
San's sister is still waiting for your apology.

39
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:39,480
What are we having for lunch?

40
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,600
Is there any fish?

41
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:50,079
Here.

42
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,840
Today is the Ghost Festival.

43
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:01,040
Wanfu's grave is not far from here.

44
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,040
I want to visit him

45
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:03,580
and burn some incense.

46
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,810
You should come too.

47
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:07,940
You can release a river lantern for your family.

48
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:34,280
Nurse Han,

49
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,120
the bullet went right through.

50
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,280
This buddy

51
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:47,850
must have fallen in battle.

52
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,120
There must have been a fight here.

53
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,080
His body

54
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:53,280
was likely washed away by the river.

55
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:03,840
This is the grave I set up for Wanfu.

56
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,480
I haven't been here for a few days,

57
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:11,280
and there are so many new graves.

58
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:19,040
I can't even read the words on the tombstones clearly.

59
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,320
Before I set up this grave,

60
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:40,360
Her Ladyship laughed at me.

61
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,000
She said I was so young

62
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:43,800
yet so feudal,

63
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,640
knowing to set up a cenotaph.

64
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:49,320
I don't even know what a cenotaph is.

65
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:51,920
I just wanted to set up a grave for Wanfu,

66
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:54,000
to have something to remember him by.

67
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,480
Wanfu had no family left,

68
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,520
and neither do I.

69
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:01,160
So Wanfu was my only family.

70
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,680
Sometimes,

71
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,360
when I feel sad,

72
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:06,240
I come here to sit for a while.

73
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:08,440
I feel like he's talking to me,

74
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:10,720
and he's right beside me.

75
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:13,120
It makes me feel at ease.

76
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,240
Nurse Han,

77
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,460
I'll call you Xiaoyue from now on.

78
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:24,420
Then I'll call you Brother Zhang.

79
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:29,040
Xiaoyue,

80
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,720
I want to thank you.

81
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,200
All the buddies of my 87th Brigade

82
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,730
died in battle in Shanghai.

83
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,640
Not even their bones remain.

84
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,159
Nothing is left.

85
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,400
But you building such a grave

86
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:43,360
for Wanfu by the Yangtze River in Wuhan

87
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:46,500
also serves as a memorial for those buddies.

88
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:48,680
Thank you.

89
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:00,700
Brother Zhang.

90
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:01,880
Look.

91
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,180
A flower is blooming here.

92
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:07,800
Do you think

93
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:10,320
this is Wanfu greeting me

94
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,400
and talking to me?

95
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:14,680
Yes.

96
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,080
It must be your Wanfu

97
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:18,760
talking to you

98
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:20,400
and greeting you.

99
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,560
He wants to tell you

100
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:25,880
that he is doing well over there.

101
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,080
Seeing you here

102
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,240
keeping busy every day

103
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,640
and able to hold your own,

104
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,160
he is relieved

105
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,280
and at peace.

106
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:38,570
I really envy you, Xiaoyue.

107
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:40,000
You are better off than me.

108
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,920
When you miss someone in your heart,

109
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,280
you at least have a place

110
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:45,220
to say what's on your mind.

111
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:46,600
My father,

112
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:48,800
my wife,

113
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:53,040
and my child whom I've never met,

114
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,860
all died by the Yangtze River in Nanjing.

115
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,940
They left nothing behind.

116
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:02,200
I have nothing.

117
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,200
I don't even have a place to talk to them.

118
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:17,690
Looking at this vast Yangtze River, I wonder.

119
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,120
This river water

120
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,640
flows by day

121
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,400
and by night.

122
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:25,420
Does it understand feelings?

123
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:27,520
Does it know the pain in my heart?

124
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,380
Does it know how much I suffer?

125
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,400
It knows.

126
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,080
It feels the pain.

127
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:47,880
Brother Zhang.

128
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:49,920
There is a custom in my hometown.

129
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:52,520
We fold grass boats during the Ghost Festival.

130
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:54,240
Using that kind of grass.

131
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,240
Just like floating river lanterns.

132
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:58,720
If you release a grass boat from Wuhan,

133
00:08:58,920 --> 00:09:00,850
it will reach Nanjing in a few days.

134
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,460
You can also send some heartfelt words over.

135
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:07,360
Right.

136
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:09,520
You're right.

137
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,240
In Wuhan today,

138
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:12,850
in Nanjing in a few days.

139
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,640
A few days later,

140
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:17,600
it will reach the sea.

141
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:22,100
It will eventually reach the sea.

142
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,300
Pick the grass.

143
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:33,820
Fold the boats.

144
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,160
You fold a big one

145
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:39,560
for your family.

146
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,090
I'll fold a small one

147
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,040
for Wanfu.

148
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,580
We'll fold many boats.

149
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:45,690
For my buddies in the 87th Brigade,

150
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:46,820
and for your Wanfu.

151
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,360
Okay.

152
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:16,960
Brother Zhang.

153
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:19,280
Can you give me this helmet?

154
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:22,980
Aren't you afraid?

155
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:24,120
No, I'm not.

156
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,680
This buddy,

157
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,330
just like Wanfu and you,

158
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:28,840
is a great hero.

159
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,800
I want to take it back,

160
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,600
plant it full of flowers,

161
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:33,970
and put it in the ward

162
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,420
for the buddies to see.

163
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:11,720
Father.

164
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:13,880
Why don't you stop waiting.

165
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:15,280
I'll let down the bedboard for you.

166
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:17,280
You rest first, I'll wait for Wanfu.

167
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,960
Let's wait together.

168
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:23,840
I'm worried too, he should be back soon.

169
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:30,600
He's back.

170
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,320
How did it go?

171
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:45,120
Messed up.

172
00:12:45,880 --> 00:12:46,760
You lost?

173
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:50,040
I lost.

174
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:54,040
Did Lingzhao Mandarin Fish lose?

175
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:57,200
And Du Le Le Zhong Le Le lost too?

176
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:02,400
Did you recite it as we told you?

177
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,560
It shouldn't be.

178
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:08,680
Shouldn't be.

179
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:11,240
Did King Wen of Zhou not work?

180
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:14,560
The dishes weren't cooked well?

181
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:15,720
They were.

182
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:17,850
Didn't recite the words right?

183
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,360
I memorized them all.

184
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:20,520
Then did you say what

185
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:22,560
I told you to say to Mr. Tian at the end?

186
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:24,440
I said it all, word for word.

187
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:30,200
What did you say? Tell me again.

188
00:13:30,280 --> 00:13:32,000
I did exactly what you said.

189
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:35,130
After I announced the dish names during the banquet,

190
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:37,680
I took the initiative to find Mr. Tian,

191
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:38,520
pulled him aside,

192
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:39,480
and I told him.

193
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:40,560
"Mr. Tian,

194
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:45,560
actually, this Meng Family Banquet

195
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,360
is just a front.

196
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:49,760
What I just said about

197
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:52,480
'The Book of Songs: Greater Court Hymns, Han Yi' and all that

198
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:56,880
was just to add some elegance to the banquet.

199
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:58,760
I don't actually know any of it,

200
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:00,760
my father and my wife taught it to me,

201
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,160
I memorized it by rote.

202
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,200
I just

203
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:06,200
cook ordinary home-style dishes."

204
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,600
When Mr. Tian heard that,

205
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:10,000
bam, he slammed the table,

206
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,530
pointed at my nose and said,

207
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:14,050
"You dared to lie to me, didn't you?

208
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:16,680
Get out of here right now!"

209
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:18,160
He said you lied to him?

210
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:23,240
This person is so shallow,

211
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:25,480
wasting our good intentions.

212
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:27,640
It's fine not to associate with him.

213
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:32,240
Father, Wanfu.

214
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:33,920
Here's what I think.

215
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:36,400
Before,

216
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,840
I thought Mr. Tian was well-informed and

217
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:41,000
certainly wouldn't make a decision so quickly

218
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,000
just because he heard a few stories.

219
00:14:43,160 --> 00:14:44,400
Now it seems

220
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:47,400
I might have been wrong.

221
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:48,880
But,

222
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:51,920
I still think we did the right thing.

223
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:54,960
We made up so many stories for these dishes,

224
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:57,760
it can add some elegance to the banquet.

225
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:59,080
But in the end,

226
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:00,800
we still had to tell the truth.

227
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:03,000
If you only know how to cook home-style dishes,

228
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:05,200
then that's what you know.

229
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:06,800
But knowing how to cook home-style dishes

230
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:09,080
is understanding the true flavor of the human world.

231
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:10,240
Isn't the duty of cooking

232
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:12,280
the same as the duty of being a person?

233
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:15,080
So Wanfu, please don't be sad.

234
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:18,120
From this perspective,

235
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:20,200
we didn't lose.

236
00:15:21,280 --> 00:15:22,920
That's right.

237
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:26,040
Exactly.

238
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:31,800
I

239
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:37,040
didn't lose. I didn't lose.

240
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:39,600
I didn't lose at all.

241
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:41,960
Mr. Tian gave me a big reward

242
00:15:42,040 --> 00:15:44,280
and made me the head chef.

243
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:46,720
He even made me the head chef.

244
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:49,000
I won the cooking competition!

245
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:49,600
I won!

246
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:51,160
Mr. Tian didn't scold me.

247
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:53,080
He gave me a big reward

248
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:54,160
and made me the head chef.

249
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:56,320
From now on, I'm in charge of the kitchen!

250
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:57,480
You brat.

251
00:15:57,560 --> 00:15:58,080
I'll beat you with the ruler.

252
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:58,960
No, Master!

253
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,480
I was wrong.

254
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,520
Madam, what's wrong?

255
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:05,760
Don't talk to me.

256
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:08,200
How childish. You're an adult.

257
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:11,640
I was just teasing you.

258
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:13,180
Madam, you don't know.

259
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:14,360
Mr. Tian heard

260
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:16,280
what you taught me to say,

261
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:18,560
and immediately pointed at me, saying,

262
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:20,720
'I like your honesty, kid.'

263
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:24,320
I just don't understand.

264
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:26,800
Why are your words so effective on Mr. Tian?

265
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:28,730
Because you're foolish. Why else?

266
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:31,640
Because you're foolish.

267
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:34,120
You really are.

268
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:38,280
A gentleman can be deceived by his own principles.

269
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:39,840
It seems now

270
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:42,080
that a bunch of flowery words

271
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:45,160
isn't as good as a sincere truth.

272
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:51,920
It seems this Mr. Tian has a promising future.

273
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,920
Very promising.

274
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,080
That's how it is.

275
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:00,320
That's how it is.

276
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:06,420
About the factory,

277
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:09,040
if President Shao and his people don't step forward,

278
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:10,839
what will Master do?

279
00:17:11,359 --> 00:17:13,240
Brown suggested to Master before

280
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:15,119
that for our factories in Pudong,

281
00:17:15,119 --> 00:17:17,720
just hanging a few foreign flags isn't enough.

282
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:20,480
It's best to find a reliable Japanese merchant

283
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:23,040
and let him have some nominal shares.

284
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:24,720
This Japanese merchant can then step forward

285
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:26,560
and negotiate with the Japanese military.

286
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:28,480
Even if we need to send money or find connections later,

287
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:29,960
it would be more convenient.

288
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,640
But Master still refused.

289
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,460
He wants to place his hopes

290
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:35,880
on President Shao.

291
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:50,620
Master might be upstairs.

292
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:52,760
This President Shao,

293
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:54,560
if he publicly turns traitor,

294
00:17:54,560 --> 00:17:56,360
half of Shanghai's industrial and commercial circles

295
00:17:56,360 --> 00:17:58,020
will be dragged down with him.

296
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:00,600
That would push us to a dead end.

297
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:03,160
As soon as the battle in Peiping started,

298
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:05,890
Master cut ties with the Japanese shareholders.

299
00:18:06,080 --> 00:18:07,680
Unless it's absolutely necessary,

300
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:09,160
Master won't let the factory

301
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:11,280
have anything to do with the Japanese.

302
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:13,010
Not all Japanese are like that.

303
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:14,000
That Kudo

304
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:15,520
has a life-and-death friendship with Master.

305
00:18:15,520 --> 00:18:16,200
Yes.

306
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:19,280
And I think he will help.

307
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:22,480
He's different from other Japanese.

308
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,440
I heard him

309
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:25,960
publicly curse the Japanese Army Headquarters,

310
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:28,920
saying those young officers who started the August 13th Incident

311
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:30,680
were utterly deranged.

312
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:33,840
I suggested this to Master before,

313
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,680
but he just wouldn't do it.

314
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,200
He said

315
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:40,120
it's the worst possible plan.

316
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:42,400
But now all the other roads

317
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:44,240
are completely blocked.

318
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:47,560
There's no other way to go.

319
00:19:23,760 --> 00:19:24,560
Sir,

320
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:26,980
would you like us to talk with you?

321
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:29,760
Press the shutter for me.

322
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:01,210
Tomorrow, accompany me

323
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:02,680
to see Mr. Kudo.

324
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:03,960
Yes.

325
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:08,520
Sir, I still have to tell you,

326
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:11,600
Wanfu's family is really too suspicious.

327
00:20:12,040 --> 00:20:13,960
Even though the old man is sickly,

328
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:15,980
just looking at his style,

329
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:18,640
he's not the same kind of person as Wanfu at all.

330
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:20,740
His wife is even more suspicious.

331
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:23,840
I saw her singing to the child yesterday,

332
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:25,880
and it was actually an English song,

333
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:27,160
and very fluently.

334
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:29,760
How does she look like a cook's wife?

335
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,480
I have to investigate carefully

336
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:33,800
whether he's from the CC Clique, the BIS,

337
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:35,600
or sent by the Japanese.

338
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:37,640
Go investigate.

339
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:40,280
As long as he's connected to

340
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:41,720
any of these three parties,

341
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:45,120
tie up the whole family and throw them into the Huangpu River.

342
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:54,400
Come.

343
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:10,160
Okay.

344
00:21:10,440 --> 00:21:11,640
Thank you, Nurse Han.

345
00:21:17,640 --> 00:21:18,560
Xiaoyue.

346
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:22,280
Miss, why are you here?

347
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:23,490
Congratulations on

348
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,360
becoming a real nurse.

349
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:27,610
I still have a long way to go.

350
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:32,970
By the way, how did your talk with Young Master Luo go?

351
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:35,240
Without love,

352
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:38,560
life is as hollow as a vase.

353
00:21:39,360 --> 00:21:41,440
When I said this line before,

354
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:44,000
I didn't understand Nora's feelings.

355
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:47,280
Miss, in my heart, you are Nora.

356
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:50,160
You taught me to be a woman of the new era,

357
00:21:50,320 --> 00:21:52,040
independent, strong, and brave.

358
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:53,400
Don't be an appendage to men.

359
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:55,200
Be a self-reliant Nora.

360
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:57,320
Silly sister, that's all acting.

361
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:59,160
You said it, it's not just a play.

362
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:01,360
It's life, a higher level of life.

363
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,330
A person should live like that.

364
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:05,920
That... that was just

365
00:22:06,080 --> 00:22:08,080
my youth, my dream.

366
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:10,860
Staying away from the war is reality.

367
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:24,080
Xiaoyue.

368
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:26,840
Are you like Zuliang,

369
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:28,770
looking down on me, a deserter?

370
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:37,800
No, Miss.

371
00:22:38,320 --> 00:22:39,640
Young Master Luo said,

372
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:42,160
all choices true to one's heart

373
00:22:42,240 --> 00:22:43,200
are brave.

374
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:44,040
Brave.

375
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:48,200
But I didn't expect either

376
00:22:48,320 --> 00:22:50,000
that I would become a deserter.

377
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,880
For you, as a souvenir.

378
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:05,720
Miss.

379
00:23:06,360 --> 00:23:09,040
Have you really decided to leave?

380
00:23:12,360 --> 00:23:13,760
This is your

381
00:23:14,840 --> 00:23:16,840
first time traveling far alone.

382
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:18,880
You must stay alert.

383
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:22,240
After you go out, don't just focus on reading

384
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:23,880
and lose your luggage.

385
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:26,240
The bag must be on your arm.

386
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:28,000
Keep the money separately.

387
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:28,760
If it's cold,

388
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:29,240
remember to put on more clothes.

389
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:32,240
Alright, my silly sister.

390
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:34,360
Why are you nagging like my mom?

391
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:35,960
And,

392
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:38,320
don't call me Miss anymore.

393
00:23:38,920 --> 00:23:39,800
Call me Sis.

394
00:23:41,080 --> 00:23:41,680
Okay.

395
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:44,880
Sis,

396
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:48,860
take care of yourself.

397
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:51,640
Take care.

398
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:05,880
Sis,

399
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:16,460
remember to write to me when you arrive in Hong Kong.

400
00:24:33,520 --> 00:24:36,480
I heard from Nurse Han that Miss Yu has left.

401
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:43,080
I don't blame Shuzhen for leaving at all.

402
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:45,000
Not everyone can be a soldier,

403
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:47,760
even if they think they are,

404
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:50,080
just like me now.

405
00:24:50,520 --> 00:24:52,400
War makes everyone of us

406
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:54,680
see our truest selves.

407
00:24:55,320 --> 00:24:56,720
In just one year,

408
00:24:56,960 --> 00:24:59,440
you've become a completely different person,

409
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:01,000
from a hot-blooded youth

410
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:03,080
into the strongest soldier.

411
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:07,480
This year has been too long.

412
00:25:08,160 --> 00:25:09,320
Yunkui,

413
00:25:10,560 --> 00:25:13,680
how much longer do we have to endure days like this?

414
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:15,000
I don't know.

415
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:17,040
Five years,

416
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:18,770
eight years, ten years,

417
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:20,320
or maybe even longer.

418
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:28,880
Sometimes,

419
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:31,760
when I look at the morgue outside the hospital,

420
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:34,080
neatly and densely packed

421
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:35,760
with the bodies of martyrs,

422
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:37,480
I actually start to envy them.

423
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:39,560
They have gone to heaven,

424
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:41,800
having completed their missions.

425
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:44,160
Those of us who survived

426
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:46,680
are the ones in hell.

427
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:48,720
We are having a hard time,

428
00:25:49,360 --> 00:25:50,920
but the enemy is having an even harder time.

429
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:53,250
Once their plan for a quick victory fails,

430
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:54,560
it will turn into a war of attrition.

431
00:25:54,560 --> 00:25:57,480
The longer the war drags on, the more advantageous it is for us.

432
00:25:57,480 --> 00:25:59,840
Time is the most favorable factor for us.

433
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:01,400
Yes.

434
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:04,760
Right now, it seems the enemy is winning battle after battle,

435
00:26:04,760 --> 00:26:06,200
occupying half of China.

436
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:08,720
But China is huge.

437
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:11,920
The larger the area they occupy,

438
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:13,960
the more difficult it becomes for them

439
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:15,520
to maintain military control over those regions.

440
00:26:15,520 --> 00:26:17,280
You know that China's economy

441
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:19,120
is primarily self-sufficient.

442
00:26:19,360 --> 00:26:20,880
As long as we can endure these sacrifices

443
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:22,040
and the pain,

444
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,760
continuously weakening their strength,

445
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:26,720
I believe victory will ultimately be ours.

446
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:30,320
We should also go behind enemy lines.

447
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:33,160
Yes, the battlefield behind enemy lines has great potential.

448
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:34,600
This is the key to our victory.

449
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:37,660
Yunkui, have you heard of The Eighth Route Army Office?

450
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:40,320
Recently, there have been a few articles in the 'Xinhua Daily'

451
00:26:40,320 --> 00:26:42,320
that share many of your views.

452
00:26:42,720 --> 00:26:45,000
Especially two articles on guerrilla warfare,

453
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:47,330
which are truly insightful and incisive.

454
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:49,400
Are you in contact with them?

455
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:50,520
Not exactly.

456
00:26:50,720 --> 00:26:52,760
Do you remember when we were at the Shanghai hospital,

457
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:54,120
I told you about

458
00:26:54,200 --> 00:26:55,760
Mr. Xie Yufeng?

459
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:57,290
He has also come to Wuhan

460
00:26:57,600 --> 00:26:58,960
and showed me an article,

461
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:00,480
'On Protracted War'.

462
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:01,680
Its insights

463
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:04,160
directly address the core of the war of resistance,

464
00:27:04,160 --> 00:27:06,680
and it is now being quietly circulated among us.

465
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:09,080
Can you let me read it to learn from it?

466
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:10,280
Of course.

467
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:11,600
In this manuscript,

468
00:27:11,600 --> 00:27:12,320
the analysis of all sectors of society

469
00:27:12,320 --> 00:27:13,840
and the overall situation of the war of resistance

470
00:27:13,840 --> 00:27:14,920
gave me a sudden realization,

471
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:16,450
as if opening up a new world.

472
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:20,160
Yunkui.

473
00:27:20,560 --> 00:27:22,520
What are you planning to do next?

474
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:25,880
In this world,

475
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:28,200
Zhang Yunkui no longer exists.

476
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:33,200
Rest assured, Mrs. Meng.

477
00:27:33,280 --> 00:27:34,000
Our Mr. Tian

478
00:27:34,040 --> 00:27:35,840
is not as scary as the rumors say.

479
00:27:35,960 --> 00:27:37,160
He's very easygoing.

480
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:39,410
He just likes to keep things clean.

481
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:40,360
Just wipe the dust off

482
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:41,760
the desk

483
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:43,360
and the books.

484
00:27:43,560 --> 00:27:44,000
Okay.

485
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:46,480
It's very clean here. We clean it every day.

486
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:48,160
Miss Sibao.

487
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:52,120
My father is taking a nap.

488
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:53,720
Wanfu is in the kitchen.

489
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:55,240
Is it okay if I bring the child

490
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:55,960
here?

491
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:56,880
It's fine.

492
00:27:56,960 --> 00:27:58,200
Just do your job well.

493
00:27:58,520 --> 00:27:58,960
Okay.

494
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:01,170
Just don't let Yueming pee in the room,

495
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:02,240
it will smell.

496
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:03,400
I won't.

497
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:06,520
I'll go clean Mr. Tian's bedroom first.

498
00:28:06,520 --> 00:28:07,160
You go ahead.

499
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:07,760
Okay.

500
00:28:50,400 --> 00:28:52,440
Yueming, do you want to hear a story?

501
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:54,640
Yes.

502
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:56,480
This story is called

503
00:28:56,480 --> 00:28:58,400
'The Little Match Girl'.

504
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:01,370
It was written by Grandpa Andersen from Denmark.

505
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:03,720
The first time Mom heard this story,

506
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:06,000
it was Dad who read it to Mom.

507
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:13,440
Dad and I both love this story so much.

508
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:14,360
Every time we hear it,

509
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,920
we cry for a long time.

510
00:29:17,040 --> 00:29:19,360
It's a story about a little girl

511
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:22,600
selling matches on Christmas Eve.

512
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:24,280
That day,

513
00:29:24,440 --> 00:29:27,720
it was very cold and snowing.

514
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,760
It was getting dark,

515
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:32,120
already evening.

516
00:29:32,360 --> 00:29:34,960
It was the last night of the year.

517
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:38,920
In this cold, gloomy time,

518
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:41,640
a poor little girl walked on the street

519
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:42,680
bareheaded

520
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:43,840
and barefoot.

521
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:46,760
When she left home,

522
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:49,090
she was originally wearing shoes.

523
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:51,680
But what use was that?

524
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:54,680
She had been wearing her mother's shoes all this time.

525
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:55,760
They were that big.

526
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:58,760
You also think she couldn't wear her mother's shoes,

527
00:29:58,760 --> 00:30:00,520
right?

528
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:04,120
The little girl saw

529
00:30:04,160 --> 00:30:06,620
two carriages galloping over on the street.

530
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:08,960
When she hurriedly ran to the other side,

531
00:30:09,280 --> 00:30:12,520
she lost her shoes.

532
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:14,280
One shoe

533
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:16,000
she could never find again.

534
00:30:17,600 --> 00:30:19,720
A little boy picked up the shoe,

535
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:21,960
held it up, and ran away.

536
00:30:22,360 --> 00:30:25,480
He also said, 'When I have a child,

537
00:30:25,880 --> 00:30:27,480
I will use it as a cradle.'

538
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:34,520
So the little girl went barefoot.

539
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:39,040
Her feet were frozen red and blue.

540
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:43,680
She's very pitiful, isn't she?

541
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:47,000
In her shabby scarf,

542
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:49,320
she carried many matches.

543
00:30:49,760 --> 00:30:52,840
But all day long, no one

544
00:30:53,040 --> 00:30:54,770
bought a single match from her,

545
00:30:54,960 --> 00:30:57,480
and no one gave her a single mace.

546
00:30:58,080 --> 00:30:59,440
Do you know why Grandpa Andersen

547
00:30:59,440 --> 00:31:01,200
wrote it this way?

548
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:02,960
Grandpa Andersen

549
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:05,760
wanted to use a small object like a shoe

550
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:08,680
to portray the girl's

551
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:10,810
pitifulness when she first appeared.

552
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:12,570
Did you understand?

553
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:16,520
I understood.

554
00:31:18,120 --> 00:31:20,280
Our Yueming is so great.

555
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:22,000
I knew you could understand.

556
00:31:22,040 --> 00:31:24,640
You are so smart, just like your father.

557
00:31:24,880 --> 00:31:25,840
Then our Yueming,

558
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:27,160
when you grow up,

559
00:31:27,280 --> 00:31:28,400
you must become

560
00:31:28,480 --> 00:31:30,280
a great hero like your father,

561
00:31:30,440 --> 00:31:31,560
okay?

562
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:39,600
Mr... Mr. Tian.

563
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:44,120
Please finish it.

564
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:50,480
I'm just teasing the child.

565
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:56,010
The child is named Yueming.

566
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:57,560
Yes, Yueming.

567
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:03,120
Yueming's father is a great hero.

568
00:32:05,920 --> 00:32:08,520
Wanfu is a great hero.

569
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,200
Wanfu

570
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:14,480
is cooking in the kitchen.

571
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:42,040
Get back to your work.

572
00:32:42,040 --> 00:32:42,720
Okay.

573
00:32:56,560 --> 00:32:57,280
Sir,

574
00:32:57,920 --> 00:32:59,180
when did you come back?

575
00:33:00,520 --> 00:33:01,640
I never left.

576
00:33:03,040 --> 00:33:03,840
I've checked.

577
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:06,840
That family definitely has no ties to the Japanese.

578
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:08,770
I'm still looking into Chongqing.

579
00:33:10,360 --> 00:33:11,360
I'll do it myself.

580
00:33:14,080 --> 00:33:15,400
Was Sibao fired too?

581
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,160
Si... No, no.

582
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:18,000
No, no, no.

583
00:33:18,040 --> 00:33:20,480
Mrs. Meng said she didn't want to eat for free.

584
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:22,200
I felt sorry for the family.

585
00:34:03,520 --> 00:34:04,680
You are...

586
00:34:04,680 --> 00:34:05,280
You are...

587
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:07,540
I'm from the Tian Mansion.

588
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:11,920
I just read and write when I have nothing to do.

589
00:34:12,199 --> 00:34:13,600
I heard we had a new neighbor,

590
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:15,130
so I came to pay my respects.

591
00:34:15,239 --> 00:34:16,840
I'd like to ask for your advice on something.

592
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:17,880
You're too polite.

593
00:34:17,880 --> 00:34:19,600
Come, please have a seat.

594
00:34:19,639 --> 00:34:20,639
Okay.

595
00:34:24,600 --> 00:34:26,480
Come, have some water.

596
00:34:27,679 --> 00:34:30,679
A friend recommended a set of books for me to collect.

597
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:33,920
I'd like to ask you to take a look at it for me

598
00:34:34,120 --> 00:34:35,580
and see if it's authentic.

599
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:38,840
I'm just a scholar.

600
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:42,199
I don't have that much knowledge. You're too polite.

601
00:34:43,600 --> 00:34:45,480
This is a Song Dynasty edition.

602
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:54,760
To get a Song Dynasty edition book in Shanghai right now

603
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:57,160
is really

604
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:59,680
not easy.

605
00:35:05,160 --> 00:35:06,680
Please take a look for me.

606
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:43,160
What a pity.

607
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:45,880
Why?

608
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:47,200
This book...

609
00:35:48,120 --> 00:35:49,250
It's not old enough.

610
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:53,600
My friend said

611
00:35:53,840 --> 00:35:55,640
if this is not from the Northern Song Dynasty,

612
00:35:55,640 --> 00:35:57,600
it must be from the Southern Song Dynasty.

613
00:35:57,600 --> 00:35:59,260
He said he picked up a bargain.

614
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:01,240
Books from the Song Dynasty

615
00:36:02,520 --> 00:36:05,520
can be divided into the Northern and Southern Song Dynasties.

616
00:36:05,520 --> 00:36:09,040
There are also several kinds of Southern Song Dynasty editions.

617
00:36:09,040 --> 00:36:11,640
There are editions printed in the Southern Song Dynasty,

618
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:14,360
those reprinted in the Yuan Dynasty,

619
00:36:15,080 --> 00:36:17,720
and replica editions.

620
00:36:18,080 --> 00:36:20,760
Your book is a replica edition.

621
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:22,480
It's not worth much.

622
00:36:23,240 --> 00:36:25,080
How can you tell?

623
00:36:27,120 --> 00:36:28,080
For this book,

624
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:32,120
first of all, you have to look at the color of the paper,

625
00:36:32,680 --> 00:36:34,680
then the carving of the characters,

626
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:37,360
as well as the block center and fishtails.

627
00:36:37,480 --> 00:36:39,520
If it were a genuine Southern Song Dynasty edition,

628
00:36:39,520 --> 00:36:44,960
first of all, the ink would be fragrant, the characters would be beautiful, elegant, and classic.

629
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:46,320
You can tell by opening the book.

630
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:47,120
Smell it.

631
00:36:47,240 --> 00:36:49,720
Is there no ink fragrance?

632
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:59,060
It's too much trouble to explain it this way.

633
00:36:59,240 --> 00:37:00,600
You can compare them.

634
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:01,920
For example,

635
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:04,050
the 'A Record of Mount Lu' I collected,

636
00:37:04,240 --> 00:37:07,570
its paper and ink are so beautiful that you can't put it down.

637
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:10,280
You collected 'A Record of Mount Lu'?

638
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:17,120
I am a poor scholar.

639
00:37:18,040 --> 00:37:19,700
I don't have any collections.

640
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:22,360
I just had the chance to see it.

641
00:37:22,840 --> 00:37:23,760
Yes.

642
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:26,120
Then my friend must have been deceived.

643
00:37:26,560 --> 00:37:27,520
He was told

644
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:30,680
this book was one of the few books

645
00:37:30,960 --> 00:37:34,160
salvaged from Hanfenlou Building

646
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:37,360
when it was set on fire by the Japanese in the 21st year of the Republic of China.

647
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:38,800
Hanfenlou Building.

648
00:37:42,240 --> 00:37:43,240
What a pity.

649
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:47,130
That was the life's work of my friend Master Zhang Yuanji

650
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:48,960
for decades.

651
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:51,280
A collection of 460,000 books,

652
00:37:51,680 --> 00:37:53,840
3,700 kinds of ancient books,

653
00:37:54,160 --> 00:37:57,880
and 35,000 volumes were destroyed in an instant.

654
00:37:58,160 --> 00:38:00,520
The five-story building was bombed into an empty shell.

655
00:38:00,520 --> 00:38:02,600
It was horrible to look at.

656
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:07,880
The Japanese deliberately bombed and burned it

657
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:11,600
to destroy traditional Chinese culture.

658
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:13,240
Those buildings in Zhabei

659
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:14,960
can be repaired in the future.

660
00:38:15,080 --> 00:38:17,720
But the treasures of Chinese culture

661
00:38:17,800 --> 00:38:19,840
can never be restored.

662
00:38:20,040 --> 00:38:20,920
Sir,

663
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:23,680
I'd like to ask you another question.

664
00:38:24,400 --> 00:38:26,240
What does it mean

665
00:38:26,600 --> 00:38:28,760
that it's easy to defeat the thief in the mountain

666
00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:30,720
but hard to defeat the thief in the mind

667
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:32,200
that you just wrote?

668
00:38:34,480 --> 00:38:38,280
As a scholar,

669
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:42,410
Master Wang Yangming could put his theory of conscience into practice

670
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:44,440
and unify knowledge and action.

671
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:46,680
As Master Zhang Taiyan said,

672
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:50,600
he dared to straighten his body and do what he wanted.

673
00:38:50,880 --> 00:38:52,680
It was like a torch in a dark room.

674
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:54,480
He is truly admirable.

675
00:38:55,040 --> 00:38:58,120
So I have always taught my son

676
00:38:58,360 --> 00:39:02,620
to be well-versed in both letters and martial arts, and apply what he learns.

677
00:39:03,200 --> 00:39:04,040
Father.

678
00:39:08,360 --> 00:39:09,200
Mr. Tian.

679
00:39:09,960 --> 00:39:11,000
Mr. Tian.

680
00:39:12,480 --> 00:39:14,960
You are Tian Jiatai.

681
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:17,920
I'm Tian. Excuse me.

682
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:21,680
I didn't introduce myself just now. Sorry for bothering you.

683
00:39:22,240 --> 00:39:24,040
I'm sorry.

684
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:25,880
This is your son?

685
00:39:29,720 --> 00:39:31,360
My son.

686
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:35,340
I was just praising you

687
00:39:35,560 --> 00:39:40,220
that you are well-versed in both letters and martial arts, and apply what you learn.

688
00:39:41,640 --> 00:39:44,640
Thanks to your guidance, Sir.

689
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:45,680
You flatter me.

690
00:39:45,840 --> 00:39:47,800
Otherwise, I'd be a sucker.

691
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:51,800
Alright. I'll come ask for advice another day.

692
00:39:52,240 --> 00:39:53,080
Farewell.

693
00:39:53,600 --> 00:39:54,200
Okay.

694
00:40:04,520 --> 00:40:05,360
Master.

695
00:40:05,880 --> 00:40:07,120
What did you say to him?

696
00:40:07,120 --> 00:40:08,440
I didn't say anything.

697
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:10,320
He just brought a book

698
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:12,600
for me to take a look.

699
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:15,280
No, if you say too much, we'll be exposed.

700
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:18,200
Then what did you hear me say?

701
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:18,800
I...

702
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:23,200
No matter.

703
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:28,760
I see this man is also a scholar.

704
00:40:38,360 --> 00:40:45,200
The crescent moon shines over many lands.

705
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:52,120
Some are happy, some are sad.

706
00:40:52,640 --> 00:41:00,000
Some couples share the same bed.

707
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:07,480
The others are scattered across different lands.

708
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:15,200
The crescent moon shines over many lands.

709
00:41:15,680 --> 00:41:22,520
Some are happy, some are sad.

710
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:23,280
Slow down.

711
00:41:23,640 --> 00:41:24,120
Okay.

712
00:41:24,200 --> 00:41:30,440
Some couples share the same bed.

713
00:41:30,520 --> 00:41:38,400
The others are scattered across different lands.

714
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:40,120
Miss Xiaoyue.

715
00:41:40,560 --> 00:41:43,160
You look so beautiful standing in the flowers.

716
00:41:43,240 --> 00:41:44,480
We can't even tell

717
00:41:44,560 --> 00:41:46,840
which is the flower and which is you.

718
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:49,600
You're such a smooth talker.

719
00:41:50,080 --> 00:41:51,880
It's from the bottom of my heart.

720
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:53,080
Miss Xiaoyue.

721
00:41:53,400 --> 00:41:55,800
Are these flowers you picked for me?

722
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:58,280
Are they to wish me a speedy recovery?

723
00:41:58,480 --> 00:42:00,480
Yes, I picked them for you.

724
00:42:00,520 --> 00:42:00,840
Look.

725
00:42:00,840 --> 00:42:02,920
Did you eat the dandelion I picked for you?

726
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:04,880
Did you eat the forsythia I picked for you?

727
00:42:04,880 --> 00:42:06,440
Did you eat the goldthread I picked for you?

728
00:42:06,440 --> 00:42:07,760
I ate them. I ate them all.

729
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:10,090
Of course I'd eat the medicine you picked.

730
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:11,800
This feeling of being cared about

731
00:42:11,800 --> 00:42:13,000
is so great.

732
00:42:13,240 --> 00:42:15,680
It warms my heart just thinking about it.

733
00:42:16,320 --> 00:42:18,120
Only by eating the medicine I picked

734
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:19,450
can your mouth be cured.

735
00:42:27,360 --> 00:42:31,520
The water is beautiful, the mountains are beautiful, and the people are even more beautiful.

736
00:42:31,520 --> 00:42:34,240
Let's go. We brought you out to walk your legs,

737
00:42:34,440 --> 00:42:35,300
not your mouth.

738
00:42:36,240 --> 00:42:38,760
Both my legs and mouth need walking.

739
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:42,280
One, two, one.

740
00:42:42,560 --> 00:42:46,320
One, two, one.

741
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:50,280
You scared me.

742
00:42:51,120 --> 00:42:52,280
Getting paid!

743
00:42:57,520 --> 00:42:59,720
What's wrong? Is the amount incorrect?

744
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:02,440
The amount is incorrect.

745
00:43:02,760 --> 00:43:03,960
There's an extra portion.
